        "abstract": [
          {
            "@lang": "en",
            "p": {
              "$": "The invention discloses a management code encryption and decryption method based on principal component analysis and Henon mapping. Based on an original chaotic encryption and decryption method, a QRcode encryption method based on the combination of principal component analysis (PCA) and chaotic encryption is provided. A QR code containing sensitive information is hidden into a QR code containing meaningless information through PCA and then a two-dimensional chaotic sequence is generated through Henon mapping to encrypt a generated image so as to achieve advantages of being good in scrambling effect, large in secret key space and the like, statistical attacks and secret key attacks can be effectively resisted, and the requirement for QR code safety in a tracing management system occasionof the whole life cycle of a battery can be met. The conclusion that the encryption effect of the method is good is obtained through evaluation from two aspects of adjacent pixel correlation and information entropy."
            }
          },
          {
            "@lang": "ol",
            "p": {
              "$": "本发明公开了一种基于主成分分析和Henon映射的管理编码加解密方法，在原有混沌加解密方法上，提出了基于主成分分析(Principal Component Analysis，PCA)和混沌加密联合的QR码加密方法，通过PCA将包含敏感信息的QR码隐藏到包含无意义信息的QR码中，再通过Henon映射产生二维混沌序列对生成图像进行加密，具有置乱效果好，密钥空间大等优点，可有效抵御统计攻击和密钥攻击，能够满足电池全生命周期的溯源管理系统场合下对QR码安全性的要求。通过从相邻像素相关性和信息熵两方面评价得出此发明加密效果良好的结论。"
            }
          }
        ]
